
RewriteEngine on

# ------------------------------- HOW DGZ ROUTING WORKS
#
# This file's only job is to decide whether a request should be handled by
# Apache directly (real files/directories) or handed to the DGZ framework
# (everything else).
#
# When a request reaches Apache:
#   1. If the path maps to a real file on disk (CSS, JS, images, etc.)
#      → Apache serves it directly. PHP never runs.
#   2. If the path maps to a real directory on disk
#      → Apache serves it directly. PHP never runs.
#   3. Everything else
#      → Forwarded to index.php. DGZ_Router takes over from there.
#
# DGZ_Router reads the full REQUEST_URI and handles all routing logic:
#   - Defined routes (routes/web.php, routes/api.php) are checked first.
#   - Automatic route discovery (controller/method/id convention) is the fallback.
#
# Because ALL routing decisions are made inside PHP, this file does not need
# to know anything about URL depth or segment counts. A single catch-all rule
# covers every possible URL — 1 segment or 10.

# ------------------------------- RULE: empty path → home
RewriteRule ^$ index.php [L]

# ------------------------------- RULE: catch-all (any depth)
# Only fires when the path is NOT a real file and NOT a real directory.
# The [L] flag stops processing further rules once this one matches.
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d
RewriteRule ^ index.php [L]

# ------------------------------- PHP upload limits
#increase the PHP max file upload size and max post size to enable the uploading of bigger files
<IfModule mod_php7.c>
   php_value upload_max_filesize 2G
   php_value post_max_size 2G
   php_value memory_limit 900M
</IfModule>
